Results: In favour of the diagnosis were:
clinical aspect: clusters of umbilicated vesicles and crusted lesions localized within the tattoo;
Tzanck smear was positive, confirming the viral etiology of the skin lesions and excluding allergy;
Patch test was interpreted negative;
DNA-PCR confirmed the herpetic etiology;
Antiviral therapy (systemic acyclovir) proved to be effective.
